<div><h3>GRK 101 - Introductory Greek I </h3>  <p><hr>Introduces the language of classical Greece. Covers the grammar and syntax of the Ancient Greek. Students read Ancient Greek texts including philosophical works such as Plato&#8217;s &#8220;Apology of Socrates and Crito,&#8221; and selections from Homer, Herodotus and the New Testament.</p>

<p>Offered Periodically</p>

